	volume = {495},
	url = {https://ui.adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2015ASPC..495....7B},
	abstract = {DACE is a facility based at the University of Geneva (CH) dedicated to extrasolar planets data visualization, exchange and analysis. It consists of a database containing data from several observation techniques like radial velocities, light curves, imaging and in the near future, astrometry and spectroscopy. DACE provides sophisticated visualization tools as well as analysis tools through a web interface. Registered users have access to their data depending on observation programs while unregistered users have access to published data. DACE is a platform of the Swiss NCCR PlanetS project, federating the Swiss expertise in Exoplanet research. In this context, DACE will be further developed including a wide range of observational and theoretical data with the tools to analyze and compare them.},
