analysis presented in Malo et al. (2013, J/ApJ/762/88), Malo et al.
(2014ApJ...792...37M), and Gagne et al. (2014, J/ApJ/783/121). The
observations were carried out in 2011-2012 at Gemini South during three
different semesters. Broadband imaging was performed with GMOS in the i'
(iG0327, 700-850 nm) and z' (zG0328, {\textgreater}850 nm) filters. The GMOS
detector is made of three 2048x4608 CCDs, with a pixel scale of
0.073"/pixel, for a total field of view of 5.5' squared.

(4 data files).},
	urldate = {2019-07-15},
