	abstract = {Clouds and hazes are ubiquitous in the atmospheres of exoplanets. 
However, as most of these planets have temperatures between 600 and 2000
K, their clouds and hazes are likely composed of exotic condensates such
as silicates, metals, and salts. We currently lack a satisfactory
